# Hotsite Coding Standards

- Implement only the active spec.
- Prefer semantic HTML and progressive enhancement.
- Preserve keyboard navigation, visible focus, reduced-motion support, and accessible names.
- Do not invent marketing copy, claims, legal text, metrics, testimonials, or customer logos.
- Use approved tokens rather than isolated visual values when a token exists.
- Avoid unnecessary dependencies and speculative abstractions.
- Keep sections composable and content separable from presentation when the design requires editable content.
- Optimize image dimensions, formats, loading priority, and alt text intentionally.
- Protect Core Web Vitals by limiting client-side JavaScript and third-party scripts.
- Never commit secrets or production credentials.
